ever%20found%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20loved%20my%20grandparents%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-mom-grandparents-help-raise-child-expectations-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeing%20raised%20by%20them%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20confusing%20to%20me%20and%20to%20every%20parent%20who%20ever%20asked%20if%20they%20could%20call%20my%20mom%20about%20a%20sleepover%20or%20check%20in%20about%20a%20bake%20sale.%20Every%20time%20I%20made%20a%20new%20friend%2C%20it%20also%20meant%20making%20a%20fresh%20introduction%20to%20my%20unusual%20family.%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%20I%20don't%20have%20a%20mother%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20remember%20saying%20so%20often%20it%20seemed%20to%20become%20a%20cursory%20part%20of%20any%20conversation%20I%20had%20with%20my%20friends'%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWho%20do%20you%20live%20with%3F%26quot%3B%20They%20would%20ask%20as%20confusion%20was%20replaced%20with%20sadness%20when%20I%20answered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20grandparents%20were%20strict%3B%20they%20came%20from%20a%20different%20generation%20when%20kids%20had%20adult%20responsibilities.%20I%20could%20cook%20dinner%20at%2010%20and%20knew%20how%20to%20wash%20and%20hang%20curtains.%20I%20spent%20the%20Saturdays%20of%20my%20youth%20cleaning%20the%20house%20alongside%20my%20grandmother%2C%20who%20believed%20cleanliness%20was%20next%20to%20Godliness.%20Sometimes%20my%20friends%20would%20come%20to%20see%20if%20I%20could%20play%2C%20and%20I%20would%20have%20to%20send%20them%20away%20in%20what%20felt%20like%20a%20Cinderella%20moment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20different%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fage-gap-friendship-mental-health-depression-support-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emy%20friends'%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20dressed%20differently%2C%20listened%20to%20music%20from%20a%20different%20era%2C%20and%20held%20beliefs%20based%20on%20how%20and%20when%20they%20were%20raised.%20My%20grandmother%20and%20grandfather%20were%20the%20children%20of%20immigrants.%20They%20had%20witnessed%20the%20Great%20Depression%20and%20World%20War%20II.%20Hard%20work%20and%20their%20belief%20in%20God%20were%20the%20standards%20they%20lived%20and%20died%20by.%20They%20didn't%20care%20to%20discuss%20mental%20health%2C%20believed%20kids%20should%20be%20seen%20and%20not%20heard%2C%20and%20we've%20always%20had%20different%20political%20views.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Nicole%20Johnson%20with%20her%20family%20sitting%20at%20a%20table%20with%20a%20birthday%20cake.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6630ef330dfb1341e9009a4c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENicole%20Johnson%20and%20her%20brother%20were%20raised%20by%20their%20grandparents.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20Nicole%20Johnson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2260676bad-45f2-478d-9a0c-d1d4de8bee55%5C%22%3EThere%20were%20benefits%20to%20being%20raised%20by%20my%20grandparents%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20being%20raised%20differently%20from%20most%20of%20my%20peers%20wasn't%20easy%2C%20it%20also%20had%20benefits.%20It%20was%20through%20my%20grandparents%20that%20I%20learned%20some%20of%20my%20greatest%20lessons.%20I%20knew%20the%20words%20to%20every%20single%20song%20from%20the%201950s%20and%201960s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20friends%20and%20I%20went%20through%20a%20phase%20where%20we%20were%20obsessed%20with%20the%201950s%2C%20I%20had%20access%20to%20people%20who%20lived%20through%20the%20era%20and%20looked%20back%20on%20it%20fondly.%20My%20grandparents%20even%20allowed%20me%20to%20have%20a%201950s%20birthday%20party%20where%20we%20played%20their%20records%20and%20learned%20their%20dances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20friends%20loved%20my%20grandparents%2C%20who%20were%20always%20eager%20to%20have%20them%20over%20for%20dinner%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpros-c